import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Fertility')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['fertility'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across all countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    data = data.groupby('year')['life_expect'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('How has life expectancy changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], c=data['year'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Years")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['country', 'fertility']].dropna()
    top_10_countries = data.nlargest(10, 'fertility')
    top_10_countries = top_10_countries.sort_values('fertility', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(top_10_countries['country'], top_10_countries['fertility'], color=plt.cm.tab10.colors)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What are the top 10 countries with the highest fertility rates?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['n_fertility'], label='Normalized Fertility Rate', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['n_life_expect'], label='Normalized Life Expectancy', color='green')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Normalized Values')
    plt.title('How does the normalized fertility rate compare to the normalized life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
